cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.NE

The paper discusses a deep learning-based MRI reconstruction technique, which suggests that it could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories. The most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) since the paper deals with image reconstruction using deep neural networks. The second likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning) since the paper discusses the use of deep learning techniques for MRI reconstruction. The third likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory) since the paper deals with data acquisition and compression in MRI. The fourth likely category is cs.MM (Multimedia) since the paper deals with image and signal processing. The fifth likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) since the paper discusses the use of neural networks for MRI reconstruction.
